28:21.617 --> 28:22.993
(MOANING)

28:24.912 --> 28:26.368
(GASPING)

28:40.845 --> 28:43.052
(CHANTING PRAYERS)

28:49.896 --> 28:52.137
(CHANTING PRAYERS)

28:57.403 --> 28:58.483
Maya!

29:00.823 --> 29:02.734
(MAYA SPEAKING SPANISH)

29:18.341 --> 29:20.252
(SINGING SPANISH SONG)

29:33.397 --> 29:35.103
(BOTH GASPING)

30:17.692 --> 30:19.683
(SOFT MUS/C PLAYING
ON RAD/O)

30:31.414 --> 30:32.574
Hey.

30:34.000 --> 30:37.618
Five-pound bag of Gummi Bears.
Receptionists love them.

30:38.462 --> 30:41.670
A well-stocked candy dish
makes them feel popular.

30:46.512 --> 30:49.629
Dad, if I told you something,
will you promise
not to freak out?

30:52.685 --> 30:54.721
My car kind of got stolen.

30:56.522 --> 30:57.637
(SIGHING)

30:57.732 --> 31:01.099
My God, Claire,
my heart just
about stopped.

31:01.235 --> 31:02.350
(EXHALES)

31:02.445 --> 31:06.313
I know. What's a stolen car
when you're running
for your life?

31:07.825 --> 31:10.862
Not that...
Look, I loved the car,

31:10.953 --> 31:12.659
and if you ever
got me another one,

31:12.747 --> 31:16.035
I promise I will
never leave it unlocked
ever again.

31:16.375 --> 31:18.787
You left it unlocked?

31:19.962 --> 31:23.705
(WHISPERING)
Claire, I have to be
able to trust you,

31:23.799 --> 31:25.505
and notjust with a car.
With everything.

31:25.593 --> 31:26.753
I know.
I made a mistake.

31:26.844 --> 31:28.004
You can't afford mistakes.

31:28.095 --> 31:29.426
"Because we're in hiding
and it's dangerous."

31:29.513 --> 31:31.549
That's right.
Great.

31:31.640 --> 31:33.221
I'm in hiding
because of something
I can do

31:33.309 --> 31:34.845
and I don't even know
what that is.

31:34.935 --> 31:36.971
You know enough.

31:38.105 --> 31:41.393
But I don't even
know how it works
or what my limits are.

31:41.484 --> 31:43.770
I mean, if I cut off my arm,
would it reattach itself,

31:43.861 --> 31:44.850
or would I grow
a new one, or...

31:44.945 --> 31:45.980
We shouldn't be
discussing this.

31:46.072 --> 31:48.358
You're the only one
I can talk to about this.

31:48.449 --> 31:51.941
I mean, I could be missing
my opportunity to help people.

31:52.036 --> 31:54.903
If my skin can grow back
after I boil it in
with the eggs,

31:54.997 --> 31:56.908
then maybe my blood
can help someone
who got burned

31:56.999 --> 31:58.330
or someone who's sick.

31:58.459 --> 32:00.450
I don't even know
if I can get sick.
That's enough, Claire.

32:00.544 --> 32:02.409
Look, you can yell at me
all you want about the car,

32:02.505 --> 32:03.494
but this is what I am!

32:03.589 --> 32:05.090
I have kept you
out of danger
your whole life

32:05.174 --> 32:06.960
so you wouldn't
have to find
your limits.

32:07.051 --> 32:08.416
Because if they find you,
that's what they'll do.

32:08.511 --> 32:10.251
They'll cut you.
They'll test you.

32:10.346 --> 32:13.133
They will push you
so far past your capacity
for pain

32:13.224 --> 32:15.510
that you'll wish
you could die.

32:16.268 --> 32:18.099
Believe me.

32:18.187 --> 32:19.427
You may feel
confined here,

32:19.522 --> 32:22.855
but this is far freer
a cage than the one
they'd put you in.

32:25.903 --> 32:28.110
I've gotta get
back to work.

32:30.991 --> 32:34.279
You and Nakamura,
witness said you had
a fight yesterday.

32:34.370 --> 32:35.576
We were old friends.

32:35.663 --> 32:38.826
Sometimes simple conversations
can be misconstrued.

32:38.916 --> 32:40.497
MATT: He said
you slapped him.

32:40.584 --> 32:43.166
He made an offhand comment
about my son's death.

32:43.254 --> 32:44.790
I found it distasteful.

32:44.880 --> 32:47.622
You're a major shareholder
in Yamagato Industries.

32:47.716 --> 32:49.798
Its stock's been
in the toilet
for months now.

32:49.885 --> 32:52.217
You think I killed
Kaito over money?

32:52.304 --> 32:54.010
Most common motives
are money and sex.

32:54.098 --> 32:57.682
Well, I don't need the money,
and Iwasn't sleeping
with him.

32:57.768 --> 32:59.850
Not for a long time.

33:03.440 --> 33:05.431
MATT: Do you
recognize
that symbol?

33:05.526 --> 33:07.983
Yes, it's the logo
of my husband's law firm.

33:08.070 --> 33:10.026
Why draw it across
Nakamura's face?

33:11.198 --> 33:12.813
I don't know.

33:13.075 --> 33:15.236
ANGELA: Because we did
something terrible,

33:15.327 --> 33:17.283
and now someone
wants revenge.

33:19.498 --> 33:24.208
Would anyone want
revenge on him maybe?
Oh you?

33:24.295 --> 33:25.785
Who said anything
about revenge?

33:25.880 --> 33:26.915
I want my lawyer now.

33:27.006 --> 33:29.213
Who wants revenge,
Mrs. Petrelli?

33:29.300 --> 33:31.507
Stand down, Parkman.
She cried uncle.

33:33.762 --> 33:36.219
ANGELA: Get out of my head!

33:38.934 --> 33:41.471
(CHATTER/NG ON POL/CE RAD/O)

33:41.562 --> 33:43.598
MATT: Mr. Petrelli.

33:45.816 --> 33:47.772
I know you.
Detective Matt Parkman.

33:47.860 --> 33:50.442
We met in Texas
when you came to lawyer
your brother out ofjail.

33:52.281 --> 33:54.567
Look, I'm sorry about Peter.

33:54.658 --> 33:56.444
Follow me.
I'll show you
to your mother.

33:56.535 --> 33:58.275
She's not gonna
wanna see me.

33:59.663 --> 34:01.619
Look, ljust came
to get her out.

34:01.707 --> 34:05.040
Then why'd she ask
us to call you?

34:05.127 --> 34:06.867
She doesn't have
anyone else.

34:08.839 --> 34:10.579
(ANGELA SCREAMING)

34:11.133 --> 34:13.124
Where is she?

34:13.969 --> 34:15.960
Mom!

34:16.722 --> 34:18.087
MATT: That's not possible.

34:18.182 --> 34:20.218
NATHAN: Mom!

34:20.309 --> 34:22.095
(ANGELA CONTINUES SCREAMING)

34:22.186 --> 34:24.268
Stand back.

34:25.731 --> 34:27.141
(GRUNTING)

34:33.405 --> 34:34.986
(CRYING)

34:35.866 --> 34:39.154
It's gonna be all right, Mom.
It's gonna be okay.

34:39.495 --> 34:40.735
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

34:40.996 --> 34:41.985
MATT: Who did this
to you, Mrs. Petrelli?

34:57.179 --> 34:58.715
Aren't you gonna
say anything?

34:58.806 --> 35:00.012
About what?

35:00.099 --> 35:02.431
About those things you did.

35:02.518 --> 35:04.099
I didn't do anything.

35:04.186 --> 35:05.301
Make up a story.

35:05.396 --> 35:07.261
Tell me you lost your memory
of tonight, too.

35:07.356 --> 35:08.766
But don't pretend
I'm stupid.

35:09.525 --> 35:10.514
(DOOR OPENING)

35:10.609 --> 35:13.942
You had to knock
the piss out of him,
didn't you?

35:14.029 --> 35:17.772
The fellow you put through
a wall was McSorley's son.

35:17.866 --> 35:20.858
A sadistic bastard,
but his old man loves him.

35:20.953 --> 35:22.568
And you just made him
even uglier.

35:22.663 --> 35:24.528
Fine, next time
I'll leave him alone
with your sister.

35:24.623 --> 35:26.614
Don't you mouth off to me.

35:26.709 --> 35:30.293
You turned a fixable
monetary problem
into a blood feud!

35:30.379 --> 35:31.619
Ricky.

35:34.842 --> 35:37.299
You're gonna
make this right.

35:37.386 --> 35:38.876
We'll do anotherjob,

35:38.971 --> 35:41.929
something big enough
we can drop a fat stack
on his desk,

35:42.016 --> 35:44.348
get him off our backs.

35:44.435 --> 35:46.346
I'm not a thief.

35:46.437 --> 35:47.472
Maybe not.

35:47.896 --> 35:50.763
But you certainly handled
those two like a pro.

35:50.858 --> 35:52.974
And that makes you
something, now,
doesn't it?

35:53.068 --> 35:55.525
What's to say I don't do
the same thing to you
and walk out of here?

35:55.612 --> 35:58.149
I thought common courtesy
would do it.

35:58.240 --> 36:01.198
No? Then maybe this.

36:03.871 --> 36:05.736
You might want this,

36:06.540 --> 36:08.576
Peter.

36:12.338 --> 36:13.498
My name's Peter?

36:13.589 --> 36:16.422
Sounds about right,
doesn't it?
Just something I read.

36:17.217 --> 36:19.833
This here's everything
you had on you
when we found you.

36:19.928 --> 36:22.670
Credit cards,
maybe a train ticket.

36:22.765 --> 36:24.096
Could even be
aloveleﬂer

36:25.100 --> 36:27.136
It's all yours.

36:27.770 --> 36:31.934
You just have to help us
with one little job.

36:32.274 --> 36:35.687
What do you say, Peter?

36:38.655 --> 36:41.863
Hello? Mr. Kensei?
Mr. Kensei?

36:41.950 --> 36:44.817
You stole my armor,
left me withal.
Who do you think you are?

36:44.912 --> 36:47.324
I only did it
to save Yaeko.

36:47.414 --> 36:51.202
And to show that
Takezo Kensei is not
a drunk but a hero.

36:51.293 --> 36:53.204
And I did.
You did?

36:53.295 --> 36:56.458
Yes, they're already
telling of your bravery.

36:58.175 --> 37:00.211
And what exactly
did I do on this day?

37:00.302 --> 37:03.886
You disarmed 11 men
and rescued a beautiful girl.

37:04.264 --> 37:07.256
